Date: Mon, 9 Dec 2024 10:05:28 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Explicitly require `pathname`

Bundler requires `pathname`, therefore it might not always be needed.
But it is right thing to not rely on Bundler internals.
---
 test/i18n/load_path_test.rb | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/test/i18n/load_path_test.rb b/test/i18n/load_path_test.rb
index ab354c0..f5aac5c 100644
--- a/test/i18n/load_path_test.rb
+++ b/test/i18n/load_path_test.rb
@@ -1,4 +1,5 @@
 require 'test_helper'
+require 'pathname'
 
 class I18nLoadPathTest < I18n::TestCase
   def setup
